        "## Linear algebra intuition\n",
        "\n",
        "For a linear model:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\hat{y} = Xw + b\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $X \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n \\times d}$, $w \\in \\mathbb{R}^{d}$, and $b \\in \\mathbb{R}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "In neural networks, we repeat this linear transform many times with nonlinear functions in between.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculus for learning\n",
        "\n",
        "## Derivative and gradient\n",
        "\n",
        "A derivative gives local slope in 1D.\n",
        "A gradient is the vector of partial derivatives:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\nabla f(\\theta) = \\left[\\frac{\\partial f}{\\partial \\theta_1}, \\dots, \\frac{\\partial f}{\\partial \\theta_p}\\right]^\\top\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The negative gradient points toward steepest local decrease.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Chain rule and backpropagation\n",
        "\n",
        "If $L$ depends on $z$, and $z$ depends on $w$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial w} = \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial z}\\frac{\\partial z}{\\partial w}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Backpropagation applies this rule layer-by-layer [@Goodfellow.Bengio.Courville.2016].\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Activation functions and why they matter\n",
        "\n",
        "Without nonlinear activations, stacked layers collapse to one linear map.\n",
        "Activations create expressive function classes.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Sigmoid\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\sigma(x)=\\frac{1}{1+e^{-x}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Range $(0,1)$, useful for binary probability outputs.\n",
        "Can saturate for large $|x|$ and produce tiny gradients.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tanh\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\tanh(x)=\\frac{e^x-e^{-x}}{e^x+e^{-x}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Range $(-1,1)$, centered around zero.\n",
        "Still saturates at extremes.\n",
        "\n",
        "## ReLU\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathrm{ReLU}(x)=\\max(0,x)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Computationally simple, sparse activations, strong default in hidden layers.\n",
        "Potential issue: dead ReLU neurons.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Softmax\n",
        "\n",
        "For logits $z_i$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathrm{softmax}(z_i)=\\frac{e^{z_i}}{\\sum_j e^{z_j}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Maps logits to a probability simplex for multiclass tasks."
      ],
