        "# Gradient descent and stochastic gradient descent\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objective\n",
        "\n",
        "Training minimizes empirical risk:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\min_\\theta \\; J(\\theta)=\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}\\ell(f_\\theta(x_i), y_i)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "## Full-batch gradient descent\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\theta_{t+1}=\\theta_t-\\eta\\nabla J(\\theta_t)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Uses all data each step. Stable but expensive for large datasets.\n",
        "\n",
        "## SGD and mini-batch SGD\n",
        "\n",
        "SGD uses one sample (or a mini-batch) per update:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\theta_{t+1}=\\theta_t-\\eta\\nabla J_{\\mathcal{B}_t}(\\theta_t)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $\\mathcal{B}_t$ is a sampled mini-batch.\n",
        "\n",
        "Why this works in practice [@datacamp_sgd_tutorial]:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Updates are cheaper.\n",
        "2. Noise can help escape poor sharp regions.\n",
        "3. Scales well to large datasets.\n",
        "\n",
        "Practical controls:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Learning rate $\\eta$\n",
        "2. Batch size\n",
        "3. Number of epochs\n",
        "4. Learning-rate schedule"
      ],
      "id": "ceb7780e"
    },
